**1. Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

*   **Count & Layers:** The main target image shows two structures.
    *   The first structure (on the left) has 7 blocks and 2 layers.
    *   The second structure (on the right) has 10 blocks and 4 layers.
*   **Spatial Relationships (First Structure):**
    *   The base layer consists of four blocks, with two orange angled blocks on the sides, and two blue rectangular blocks in the middle of those angled blocks.
    *   The top layer consists of one green square block positioned on top of the two blue blocks.
*   **Spatial Relationships (Second Structure):**
    *   The bottom layer consists of two blocks, one yellow block on the right and one red block containing a hole in the middle of the structure.
    *   The second layer consists of four blocks: two orange blocks on the sides, one blue block on the top of the red block, and one red block that forms the lower part of the hole.
    *   The third layer consists of three blocks: one green block, one orange block on the top-right corner, and one blue block on the top-left corner.
    *   The top layer consists of one orange block, completing the roof of the structure.

**2. Select the Required Blocks from the Dictionary:**

*   **First Structure:**
    *   Block Index 12 (orange angled blocks) - used 2 times
    *   Block Index 7 (blue block) - used 2 times
    *   Block Index 5 (green block) - used 1 time
*   **Second Structure:**
    *   Block Index 2 (red block with hole) - used 1 time
    *   Block Index 11 (orange block) - used 2 times
    *   Block Index 4 (blue block) - used 2 times
    *   Block Index 6 (yellow block) - used 1 time
    *   Block Index 3 (red block for hole) - used 1 time
    *   Block Index 5 (green block) - used 1 time
